ActAppropriation Act No. 1, 2010-11
PrecisAppointment of GREGORY GOLDHAWK as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Mongolia; TAMARA GUTTMAN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Hungary, with concurrent accreditation to the Republic of Slovenia and Bosnia and Herzegovina; JAMES LAMBERT as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Kingdom of the Netherlands, with concurrent accreditation as Permanent Representative of Canada to the Organization for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons; ALAIN LATULIPPE as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Mozambique; JOHN SLOAN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Russian Federation, with concurrent accreditation to the Republic of Armenia; and DEBORAH CHATSIS as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Socialist Republic of Vietnam. .
